---
import { useTranslations, type Locale } from "../../i18n/ui";

interface Props {
  lang: Locale;
}
const { lang } = Astro.props;
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-12">
  <p class="eyebrow">{t("nav.about")}</p>
  <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold text-ink">
    {t("about.title")}
  </h1>

  {
    lang === "bs" ? (
      <div class="prose surface-panel mt-6 max-w-none p-5 text-ink sm:p-7">
        <p>
          Ovo je živi zapis o porodici Ribić – Kifić iz Jezera, koji svi zajedno
          čuvamo. Loza seže od jezerskog kadije Avde »Avdikadije« (1775–1852) pa
          sve do danas.
        </p>
        <p>
          Najveći dio ove građe zabilježili su Rasim Ribić i njegov sin Enes —
          tekstove o Avdikadiji, Akifu, Avdi Kifinu, amidži Esedu i drugima.
          Ovdje su sačuvani u izvornom obliku.
        </p>
        <p>
          Svaka osoba je jedan tekstualni fajl, a cijela stranica — stablo,
          profili, veze — gradi se iz tih fajlova. Ako znaš nešto što mi ne znamo
          — datum, priču, rođaka kojeg smo propustili — najlakše je popuniti
          formu <a href="/add">Dodaj osobu</a>. Pregledat ćemo i uvrstiti u
          stablo.
        </p>
        <p>
          Cijelo stablo i svi podaci dostupni su otvoreno na <a
            href="https://github.com/ribice/tree">GitHubu</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    ) : (
      <div class="prose surface-panel mt-6 max-w-none p-5 text-ink sm:p-7">
        <p>
          This is a living record of the Ribić – Kifić family from Jezero, kept
          by all of us. The line reaches from Avdo »Avdikadija«, the kadi of
          Jezero (1775–1852), all the way to today.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most of this material was recorded by Rasim Ribić and his son Enes —
          the texts about Avdikadija, Akif, Avdo Kifin, uncle Esed and others.
          They are preserved here in their original form (translated into
          English alongside the Bosnian).
        </p>
        <p>
          Each person is a single text file, and the whole site — tree, profiles,
          relationships — is generated from those files. If you know something we
          don't — a date, a story, a relative we've missed — the easiest way is to
          fill in the <a href="/en/add">Add a person</a> form. We'll review it and
          add it to the tree.
        </p>
        <p>
          The whole tree and all its data are openly available on <a
            href="https://github.com/ribice/tree">GitHub</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    )
  }
</article>
